--- OVERVIEW: Train_PPiMg2_LFER ---

New content synced from MareNostrum 5 (supervisor's account uv169161, reserved area
/gpfs/scratch/uv36/adrian/deepmd-training/Train_PPiMg2), on 05/07/2026. This is a free-energy
(LFER — Linear Free Energy Relationship) analysis of the pph4 reaction pathway, and a
comparison of three candidate NNP committees for that analysis. Only the resulting plots and
the analysis scripts were copied locally (the underlying umbrella-sampling/SMD trajectories,
COLVAR/KERNELS files, and the trained graph_*.pb NNP models themselves remain on the cluster
only — see conversation/session notes on repo size).

--- LFER_3_mg2/pph4/ ---

Free-energy-surface (FES) and potential-of-mean-force (PMF) analysis for the pph4 system:
o FES_2D.png: 2D free-energy surface for the reaction coordinate pair used to characterize
  the pph4 hydrolysis mechanism.
o rep_1/, rep_2/, rep_3/ (and their _tot_constrained variants, each with original/ and
  pph3_included/ sub-variants): independent replicas of the FES_2D reconstruction, testing
  sensitivity to constraints and to including the pph3 dataset in training.
o PMF_react_TS1/USW_100_react_TS1/: umbrella-sampling (window width 100) PMF along the
  reactant -> TS1 path, with an averaged profile (average_pmf.png) and per-replica WHAM
  output (rep1/2/3/WHAM/: wham_F_profile*.png free-energy profile, wham_F_windows*.png
  per-window histograms, wham_biased_P_windows*.png biased probability distributions,
  wham_cvg*.png convergence check).
o US/USW_100_TS1_TS2/, US/USW_100_TS1_TS3/, US/USW_100_TS2_TS3/: umbrella-sampling PMF scans
  between the three stationary points (TS1, TS2, TS3) of the reaction, each with the same
  average_pmf.png + per-replica WHAM plot structure as above.

--- NNP_LFER_choice/ ---

Comparison of three candidate NNP committees (NNP_1/, NNP_2/, NNP_3/) on the same
umbrella-sampling PMF reconstruction, used to select which committee to carry forward for
production LFER analysis. Each NNP_n/ contains an averaged PMF (average_pmf.png) and
per-replica WHAM diagnostics (rep_1/2/3/WHAM/), following the same plot set as above.

--- scripts/ ---

Analysis code used to produce the plots above — see scripts/README for details.

Note: this README was written on 05/07/2026 to summarize newly-synced content; no existing
local file was modified to produce it.
